NAME
       fnmatch - match a filename against a shell pattern

SYNOPSIS
       #include <fnmatch.h>

       int fnmatch(const char *pattern, const char *string, int flags);

DESCRIPTION
       Tests whether string matches the shell-style pattern. Patterns
       support the wildcards *, ?, character classes [abc] / [a-z] /
       [!abc], and backslash escapes (unless FNM_NOESCAPE).

FLAGS
       FNM_PATHNAME    '*' and '?' do not match '/'
       FNM_NOESCAPE    treat '\\' as a literal
       FNM_PERIOD      a leading '.' must be matched literally
       FNM_CASEFOLD    case-insensitive match
       FNM_LEADING_DIR pattern matches a prefix of string ending at '/'

RETURN VALUE
       0 on match, FNM_NOMATCH otherwise.

SEE ALSO
       regex(3), find(1)
